30/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Interior Minister Hari Kostov and his visiting Slovene counterpart, Rado Bohinc, agreed Tuesday (29 July) to intensify joint efforts to fight illegal migration. 
According to Bohinc, Macedonian citizens rank second in terms of illegal migration in Slovenia. 
He and Kostov also reviewed possible co-operation in improving regional security and fighting organised crime. 
In addition, Bohinc met with Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 30/07/03; MIA, A1 TV - 29/07/03)
